assetProfile.longBusinessSummary: JK Holdings Co., Ltd., through its subsidiaries, engages in the wholesale, plywood manufacturing and wood processing, franchise, construction works, and other businesses in Japan. The company produces and sells building materials; and sells housing equipment and fixtures, street signs and traffic safety equipment, construction equipment and tools, and medical equipment. It is also involved in the civil engineering construction, interior decor construction, finishing construction, buildings design and administration, forestry, residential land development, warehouse and transport, and casualty insurance agency and life insurance related businesses, as well as sale, exchange, lease, and management of real estate. In addition, the company produces and sells various plywood and structural laminated veneer lumber; and processes and sells building materials, lumber, panels, etc. Further, it is involved in the development of stores under the House Depot name and logo mark; stocking common products and handling original products; networking the financial and sales management system; implementing monthly reports and training sessions; upgrading employee hiring, training and development, and welfare benefits; promotion of new systems for housing construction and sales; upgrading services for home purchasers; and measures for the global environment and ecology. Additionally, the company operates directly managed offices for custom homes and remodeling/reconstruction of homes; provides home loans and guarantees; offers housing completion guarantee, performance indication system, after service and maintenance, etc. for home purchasers. JK Holdings Co., Ltd. was founded in 1937 and is headquartered in Tokyo, Japan.
